<item>
            <title>[STORM-3436] TupleInfo.id is not set, making debugging more difficult than it should be</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/STORM-3436</link>
                <project id="12314820" key="STORM">Apache Storm</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;TupleInfo has an id field, which is supposed to contain the tuple root id. This is printed when we enable topology debug logging, and is supposed to make it easier to track down e.g. why a tuple timed out.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We currently don&apos;t set this field, so it&apos;s always null. The logs end up looking like&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2019-06-29 11:26:31.990 o.a.s.e.s.SpoutExecutor Thread-14-kafka_spout-executor&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;4, 4&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;INFO&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; SPOUT Acking message null &lt;/p&gt;
{topic-partition=kafka-spout-test-0, offset=28, numFails=0, nullTuple=false}

&lt;p&gt;The message doesn&apos;t contain the root id, and is therefore not useful for debugging.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
